# EasyHealth Hackathon MVP

## Product scope (do not expand without explicit request)

- EN-first wellness/PHR app for EU/US - **not** a diagnostic or treatment product
- Minimal hackathon slice: wallet auth → pay-per-upload OCR → health card → x402 doctor summary
- Out of scope: family profiles, DICOM, genetics, wearables, doctor portal, B2B, RU localization

## Stack (use these, do not substitute)

- **App**: Next.js App Router (fork of `vercel-labs/x402-ai-starter`)
- **Payments**: x402 on **Arc Network**; [Circle user-controlled wallets](https://developers.circle.com/wallets/user-controlled) for auth; [Circle App Kit](https://docs.arc.io/app-kit) for Arc USDC flows if bridging needed
- **Data**: Supabase (Postgres + Storage + RLS)
- **AI**: Vercel AI SDK, single LLM call with structured JSON (Zod schema) for extraction
- **Charts**: Recharts

## Payment endpoints

| Endpoint | Price | Purpose |
|----------|-------|---------|
| `POST /api/upload` | $0.01 USDC | Pay before OCR/parsing |
| `POST /api/doctor-summary` | $0.05 USDC | Hero hackathon endpoint |

Unpaid requests MUST return HTTP 402. Never skip x402 middleware on these routes.

## Medical safety (mandatory in all AI outputs)

- Educational / health literacy language only
- NO diagnoses, prescriptions, treatment plans, or risk scores
- Always cite source document dates and biomarker values
- Always append: "This is not medical advice. Consult a healthcare professional."
- Never write PHI or health data on-chain - only payment receipts/metadata

## Data model conventions

- `profiles.wallet_address` is the auth key (unique)
- Upsert observations by `profile_id + biomarker_key + observed_at`
- Normalize `biomarker_key` to lowercase snake_case
- Original files in Supabase Storage private bucket; RLS on all tables

## Implementation discipline

- Minimize diff scope; match x402-ai-starter patterns
- Prefer sync processing with loading UI over job queues for hackathon
- Keep files < 10 MB; validate PDF/JPEG/PNG only
- Active OpenSpec change: `openspec/changes/hackathon-mvp/` - read proposal/design/specs before implementing
